+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PchzMuwgg7Reru4Q2aCUay","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-collab-editor.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9afc7e8f-bb6c-44d5-b274-f24facf40226","uuid":"f7f6043e-7da1-42c8-907a-d8e5d130a28b","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-collab-editor.md","content":"# Collaborative Document Editor Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a real-time collaborative document editing server with REST API, WebSocket collaboration, Operational Transform conflict resolution, and SQLite persistence.\n\n**Architecture:** Single Express server handles REST API for document CRUD; WebSocket connections are routed by document ID via the `ws` library attached to the HTTP server. Operational Transform (server-authoritative) ensures concurrent edits converge: each operation carries the client's known document version, and the server transforms it against any concurrent operations before applying and broadcasting.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript, Express, ws, better-sqlite3, Vitest for testing, supertest for HTTP tests.\n\n---\n\n## Module Overview\n\n```\nsrc/\n  db.ts          - Database initialization and access\n  ot.ts          - Operational Transform types and transform() function\n  documents.ts   - Document CRUD operations (DB layer)\n  server.ts      - createApp() factory: Express routes + WebSocket handling\ntests/\n  ot.test.ts     - OT transform correctness tests\n  documents.test.ts - REST API tests\n  websocket.test.ts - WebSocket collaboration tests\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: OT Core (ot.ts)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/ot.ts`\n- Create: `tests/ot.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** none\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests for OT transform**\n\nCreate `tests/ot.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { transform, applyOp, type Operation } from '../src/ot.js';\n\ndescribe('applyOp', () => {\n  it('applies insert at position 0', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello', { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'say ' })).toBe('say hello');\n  });\n\n  it('applies insert at end', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello', { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: '!' })).toBe('hello!');\n  });\n\n  it('applies delete', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello world', { type: 'delete', pos: 5, length: 6 })).toBe('hello');\n  });\n\n  it('applies delete at position 0', () => {\n    expect(applyOp('hello', { type: 'delete', pos: 0, length: 2 })).toBe('llo');\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('transform', () => {\n  it('transforms concurrent inserts at same position (insert wins by tiebreak)', () => {\n    const opA: Operation = { type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'X' };\n    const opB: Operation = { type: 'insert', pos: 3, text: 'Y' };\n    // A is server-applied; transform B against A\n    const [bPrime] = transform(opB, opA);\n    // After A inserts 'X' at 3, B should insert at 4\n    expect(bPrime).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 4, text: 'Y' });\n  });\n\n  it('transforms insert against prior insert before it', () => {\n    const opA: Operation = { type: 'insert', pos: 1, text: 'XY' };\n    const opB: Operation = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'Z' };\n    const [bPrime] = transform(opB, opA);\n    expect(bPrime).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 7, text: 'Z' });\n  });\n\n  it('transforms insert against prior insert after it (no shift)', () => {\n    const opA: Operation = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'XY' };\n    const opB: Operation = { type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'Z' };\n    const [bPrime] = transform(opB, opA);\n    expect(bPrime).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'Z' });\n  });\n\n  it('transforms insert against delete before it', () => {\n    const opA: Operation = { type: 'delete', pos: 0, length: 3 };\n    const opB: Operation = { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'X' };\n    const [bPrime] = transform(opB, opA);\n    expect(bPrime).toEqual({ type: 'insert', pos: 2, text: 'X' });\n  });\n\n  it('transforms delete against insert before it', () => {\n    const opA: Operation = { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'XY' };\n    const opB: Operation = { type: 'delete', pos: 3, length: 2 };\n    const [bPrime] = transform(opB, opA);\n    expect(bPrime).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 5, length: 2 });\n  });\n\n  it('transforms concurrent deletes at same range (idempotent)', () => {\n    const opA: Operation = { type: 'delete', pos: 2, length: 3 };\n    const opB: Operation = { type: 'delete', pos: 2, length: 3 };\n    const [bPrime] = transform(opB, opA);\n    // After A deletes chars 2-4, B's delete covers same range → noop (length 0)\n    expect(bPrime).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 2, length: 0 });\n  });\n\n  it('handles delete overlapping with prior delete', () => {\n    // opA deletes chars 2-4 (length 3), opB deletes chars 0-3 (length 4)\n    const opA: Operation = { type: 'delete', pos: 2, length: 3 };\n    const opB: Operation = { type: 'delete', pos: 0, length: 4 };\n    const [bPrime] = transform(opB, opA);\n    // opB originally covers 0-3; opA removed 2-4\n    // The overlap is 2-3 (2 chars removed by A from B's range)\n    // B's remaining range: 0-1 (length 2)\n    expect(bPrime).toEqual({ type: 'delete', pos: 0, length: 2 });\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/ot.test.ts 2>&1 | head -20\n```\nExpected: FAIL with \"Cannot find module\"\n\n**Step 3: Implement src/ot.ts**\n\n```typescript\nexport type InsertOp = { type: 'insert'; pos: number; text: string };\nexport type DeleteOp = { type: 'delete'; pos: number; length: number };\nexport type Operation = InsertOp | DeleteOp;\n\nexport function applyOp(doc: string, op: Operation): string {\n  if (op.type === 'insert') {\n    const pos = Math.min(op.pos, doc.length);\n    return doc.slice(0, pos) + op.text + doc.slice(pos);\n  } else {\n    const pos = Math.min(op.pos, doc.length);\n    const end = Math.min(pos + op.length, doc.length);\n    return doc.slice(0, pos) + doc.slice(end);\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * transform(clientOp, serverOp) → [clientOp', serverOp']\n * Returns the transformed client op to apply after serverOp has been applied.\n * Uses server-wins tiebreaking for concurrent inserts at same position.\n */\nexport function transform(clientOp: Operation, serverOp: Operation): [Operation, Operation] {\n  if (clientOp.type === 'insert' && serverOp.type === 'insert') {\n    // server insert is already applied; shift client insert if needed\n    if (serverOp.pos < clientOp.pos || serverOp.pos === clientOp.pos) {\n      // server wins tiebreak: if same pos, server goes first → client shifts right\n      return [\n        { ...clientOp, pos: clientOp.pos + serverOp.text.length },\n        serverOp,\n      ];\n    }\n    return [clientOp, serverOp];\n  }\n\n  if (clientOp.type === 'insert' && serverOp.type === 'delete') {\n    if (serverOp.pos + serverOp.length <= clientOp.pos) {\n      // server delete entirely before client insert\n      return [{ ...clientOp, pos: clientOp.pos - serverOp.length }, serverOp];\n    } else if (serverOp.pos >= clientOp.pos) {\n      // server delete entirely after client insert\n      return [clientOp, serverOp];\n    } else {\n      // client insert is within deleted range → move to start of deleted region\n      return [{ ...clientOp, pos: serverOp.pos }, serverOp];\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (clientOp.type === 'delete' && serverOp.type === 'insert') {\n    if (serverOp.pos <= clientOp.pos) {\n      // server insert before client delete → shift client delete right\n      return [{ ...clientOp, pos: clientOp.pos + serverOp.text.length }, serverOp];\n    } else if (serverOp.pos >= clientOp.pos + clientOp.length) {\n      // server insert after client delete → no change\n      return [clientOp, serverOp];\n    } else {\n      // server insert inside client delete range → extend client delete\n      return [{ ...clientOp, length: clientOp.length + serverOp.text.length }, serverOp];\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Both deletes\n  if (clientOp.type === 'delete' && serverOp.type === 'delete') {\n    const cStart = clientOp.pos;\n    const cEnd = clientOp.pos + clientOp.length;\n    const sStart = serverOp.pos;\n    const sEnd = serverOp.pos + serverOp.length;\n\n    if (sEnd <= cStart) {\n      // server delete entirely before client delete\n      return [{ ...clientOp, pos: clientOp.pos - serverOp.length }, serverOp];\n    } else if (sStart >= cEnd) {\n      // server delete entirely after client delete\n      return [clientOp, serverOp];\n    } else {\n      // overlapping deletes - compute new client delete after server already removed chars\n      const newStart = Math.min(cStart, sStart);\n      // chars in client range that server already deleted = overlap\n      const overlapStart = Math.max(cStart, sStart);\n      const overlapEnd = Math.min(cEnd, sEnd);\n      const overlap = Math.max(0, overlapEnd - overlapStart);\n      const newLength = clientOp.length - overlap;\n      // adjust position: chars before cStart that were deleted by server\n      const deletedBeforeClient = Math.max(0, Math.min(sEnd, cStart) - sStart);\n      return [{ ...clientOp, pos: cStart - deletedBeforeClient, length: Math.max(0, newLength) }, serverOp];\n    }\n  }\n\n  return [clientOp, serverOp];\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/ot.test.ts 2>&1\n```\nExpected: All OT tests pass\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/ot.ts tests/ot.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add OT core (applyOp + transform)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Database Layer (db.ts + documents.ts)\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/db.ts`\n- Create: `src/documents.ts`\n- Create: `tests/documents.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 1\n\n**Step 1: Write failing tests**\n\nCreate `tests/documents.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { initDb } from '../src/db.js';\nimport {\n  createDocument,\n  getDocument,\n  listDocuments,\n  updateDocument,\n  deleteDocument,\n  getVersionHistory,\n} from '../src/documents.js';\nimport type Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nlet db: Database.Database;\n\nbeforeEach(() => {\n  db = initDb(':memory:');\n});\n\nafterEach(() => {\n  db.close();\n});\n\ndescribe('createDocument', () => {\n  it('creates a document and returns it', () => {\n    const doc = createDocument(db, 'My Doc', 'Hello world');\n    expect(doc.id).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(doc.title).toBe('My Doc');\n    expect(doc.content).toBe('Hello world');\n    expect(doc.version).toBe(1);\n  });\n\n  it('creates a document with empty content by default', () => {\n    const doc = createDocument(db, 'Empty', '');\n    expect(doc.content).toBe('');\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('getDocument', () => {\n  it('returns null for nonexistent document', () => {\n    expect(getDocument(db, 'nonexistent')).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('returns the document', () => {\n    const created = createDocument(db, 'Test', 'content');\n    const fetched = getDocument(db, created.id);\n    expect(fetched?.id).toBe(created.id);\n    expect(fetched?.title).toBe('Test');\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('listDocuments', () => {\n  it('returns empty array when no documents', () => {\n    expect(listDocuments(db)).toEqual([]);\n  });\n\n  it('lists all documents', () => {\n    createDocument(db, 'A', '');\n    createDocument(db, 'B', '');\n    const docs = listDocuments(db);\n    expect(docs).toHaveLength(2);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('updateDocument', () => {\n  it('updates content and increments version', () => {\n    const doc = createDocument(db, 'Doc', 'hello');\n    const updated = updateDocument(db, doc.id, 'hello world', { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' });\n    expect(updated?.content).toBe('hello world');\n    expect(updated?.version).toBe(2);\n  });\n\n  it('returns null for nonexistent document', () => {\n    const result = updateDocument(db, 'missing', 'x', { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'x' });\n    expect(result).toBeNull();\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('deleteDocument', () => {\n  it('deletes a document', () => {\n    const doc = createDocument(db, 'Doc', 'hello');\n    deleteDocument(db, doc.id);\n    expect(getDocument(db, doc.id)).toBeNull();\n  });\n\n  it('returns false for nonexistent document', () => {\n    expect(deleteDocument(db, 'missing')).toBe(false);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('getVersionHistory', () => {\n  it('returns version history', () => {\n    const doc = createDocument(db, 'Doc', 'hello');\n    updateDocument(db, doc.id, 'hello world', { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' });\n    const history = getVersionHistory(db, doc.id);\n    expect(history).toHaveLength(2);\n    expect(history[0].version).toBe(1);\n    expect(history[1].version).toBe(2);\n    expect(history[1].content).toBe('hello world');\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/documents.test.ts 2>&1 | head -20\n```\n\n**Step 3: Implement src/db.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { readFileSync } from 'fs';\nimport { fileURLToPath } from 'url';\nimport { join, dirname } from 'path';\n\nconst __dirname = dirname(fileURLToPath(import.meta.url));\n\nexport function initDb(dbPath: string): Database.Database {\n  const db = new Database(dbPath);\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n  const schema = readFileSync(join(__dirname, '..', 'schema.sql'), 'utf8');\n  db.exec(schema);\n  return db;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Implement src/documents.ts**\n\n```typescript\nimport type Database from 'better-sqlite3';\nimport { randomUUID } from 'crypto';\nimport type { Operation } from './ot.js';\n\nexport interface Document {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;\n  version: number;\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\nexport interface VersionEntry {\n  version: number;\n  content: string;\n  operation: Operation | null;\n  created_at: string;\n}\n\ninterface DocRow {\n  id: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;\n  version: number;\n  created_at: string;\n  updated_at: string;\n}\n\ninterface VersionRow {\n  version: number;\n  content: string;\n  operation: string | null;\n  created_at: string;\n}\n\nexport function createDocument(db: Database.Database, title: string, content: string): Document {\n  const id = randomUUID();\n  const now = new Date().toISOString();\n\n  db.prepare(\n    `INSERT INTO documents (id, title, content, version, created_at, updated_at)\n     VALUES (?, ?, ?, 1, ?, ?)`\n  ).run(id, title, content, now, now);\n\n  db.prepare(\n    `INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation, created_at)\n     VALUES (?, 1, ?, NULL, ?)`\n  ).run(id, content, now);\n\n  return { id, title, content, version: 1, created_at: now, updated_at: now };\n}\n\nexport function getDocument(db: Database.Database, id: string): Document | null {\n  const row = db.prepare(\n    `SELECT id, title, content, version, created_at, updated_at FROM documents WHERE id = ?`\n  ).get(id) as DocRow | undefined;\n  return row ?? null;\n}\n\nexport function listDocuments(db: Database.Database): Document[] {\n  return db.prepare(\n    `SELECT id, title, content, version, created_at, updated_at FROM documents ORDER BY created_at DESC`\n  ).all() as DocRow[];\n}\n\nexport function updateDocument(\n  db: Database.Database,\n  id: string,\n  newContent: string,\n  op: Operation\n): Document | null {\n  const existing = getDocument(db, id);\n  if (!existing) return null;\n\n  const newVersion = existing.version + 1;\n  const now = new Date().toISOString();\n\n  db.prepare(\n    `UPDATE documents SET content = ?, version = ?, updated_at = ? WHERE id = ?`\n  ).run(newContent, newVersion, now, id);\n\n  db.prepare(\n    `INSERT INTO versions (document_id, version, content, operation, created_at)\n     VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?)`\n  ).run(id, newVersion, newContent, JSON.stringify(op), now);\n\n  return { ...existing, content: newContent, version: newVersion, updated_at: now };\n}\n\nexport function deleteDocument(db: Database.Database, id: string): boolean {\n  const result = db.prepare(`DELETE FROM documents WHERE id = ?`).run(id);\n  return result.changes > 0;\n}\n\nexport function getVersionHistory(db: Database.Database, docId: string): VersionEntry[] {\n  const rows = db.prepare(\n    `SELECT version, content, operation, created_at FROM versions WHERE document_id = ? ORDER BY version ASC`\n  ).all(docId) as VersionRow[];\n  return rows.map(r => ({\n    version: r.version,\n    content: r.content,\n    operation: r.operation ? JSON.parse(r.operation) as Operation : null,\n    created_at: r.created_at,\n  }));\n}\n```\n\nNote: The schema.sql doesn't have a `version` column on `documents`. We need to add it. Modify the schema.sql or handle it in initDb. The plan will use a migration approach in initDb:\n\nIn `src/db.ts`, after running schema.sql, run:\n```sql\nALTER TABLE documents ADD COLUMN version INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1;\n```\nBut only if the column doesn't exist. Use `PRAGMA table_info` to check.\n\nActually - simpler: just add `version INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1` to schema.sql since we own it.\n\n**Step 5: Update schema.sql to add version column**\n\nEdit `schema.sql`, change the documents table to:\n```sql\nCREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS documents (\n  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n  title TEXT NOT NULL,\n  content TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT '',\n  version INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,\n  created_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n  updated_at TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n);\n```\n\n**Step 6: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/documents.test.ts 2>&1\n```\nExpected: All document tests pass\n\n**Step 7: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/db.ts src/documents.ts schema.sql tests/documents.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add database layer and document CRUD\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Main Server (server.ts) - REST API\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/server.ts`\n- Create: `tests/rest.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 2\n\n**Step 1: Write failing REST API tests**\n\nCreate `tests/rest.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../src/server.js';\n\nlet app: Awaited<ReturnType<typeof createApp>>;\n\nbeforeEach(() => {\n  app = createApp(':memory:');\n});\n\nafterEach(async () => {\n  await app.stop();\n});\n\ndescribe('POST /documents', () => {\n  it('creates a document', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'My Doc', content: 'Hello' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n    expect(res.body.id).toBeTruthy();\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('My Doc');\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('Hello');\n  });\n\n  it('rejects missing title', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ content: 'Hello' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(400);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('GET /documents', () => {\n  it('lists documents', async () => {\n    await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'A', content: '' });\n    await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'B', content: '' });\n    const res = await request(app.app).get('/documents');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body).toHaveLength(2);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('GET /documents/:id', () => {\n  it('returns a document', async () => {\n    const created = await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Doc', content: 'hi' });\n    const res = await request(app.app).get(`/documents/${created.body.id}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.content).toBe('hi');\n  });\n\n  it('returns 404 for missing doc', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app.app).get('/documents/nonexistent');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('PUT /documents/:id', () => {\n  it('updates a document title', async () => {\n    const created = await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Old', content: 'hi' });\n    const res = await request(app.app)\n      .put(`/documents/${created.body.id}`)\n      .send({ title: 'New', content: 'hi' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body.title).toBe('New');\n  });\n\n  it('returns 404 for missing doc', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app.app).put('/documents/missing').send({ title: 'X', content: 'y' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('DELETE /documents/:id', () => {\n  it('deletes a document', async () => {\n    const created = await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Doc', content: '' });\n    const res = await request(app.app).delete(`/documents/${created.body.id}`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(204);\n  });\n\n  it('returns 404 for missing doc', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app.app).delete('/documents/missing');\n    expect(res.status).toBe(404);\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('GET /documents/:id/history', () => {\n  it('returns version history', async () => {\n    const created = await request(app.app).post('/documents').send({ title: 'Doc', content: 'v1' });\n    const id = created.body.id;\n    const res = await request(app.app).get(`/documents/${id}/history`);\n    expect(res.status).toBe(200);\n    expect(res.body).toHaveLength(1);\n    expect(res.body[0].version).toBe(1);\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests to verify they fail**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/rest.test.ts 2>&1 | head -20\n```\n\n**Step 3: Implement src/server.ts (REST portion)**\n\n```typescript\nimport express from 'express';\nimport { createServer } from 'http';\nimport { WebSocketServer, WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport { initDb } from './db.js';\nimport {\n  createDocument,\n  getDocument,\n  listDocuments,\n  updateDocument,\n  deleteDocument,\n  getVersionHistory,\n  type Document,\n} from './documents.js';\nimport { transform, applyOp, type Operation } from './ot.js';\nimport type Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\ninterface AppInstance {\n  app: express.Application;\n  start: (port?: number) => Promise<number>;\n  stop: () => Promise<void>;\n}\n\ninterface ClientState {\n  ws: WebSocket;\n  docId: string;\n  version: number; // last known server version\n}\n\n// Per-document state: pending ops since version N\ninterface DocSession {\n  clients: Set<ClientState>;\n}\n\nexport function createApp(dbPath = './collab.db'): AppInstance {\n  const db = initDb(dbPath);\n  const expressApp = express();\n  expressApp.use(express.json());\n\n  const httpServer = createServer(expressApp);\n  const wss = new WebSocketServer({ noServer: true });\n\n  const docSessions = new Map<string, DocSession>();\n\n  // --- REST Routes ---\n\n  expressApp.post('/documents', (req, res) => {\n    const { title, content = '' } = req.body as { title?: string; content?: string };\n    if (!title || typeof title !== 'string') {\n      res.status(400).json({ error: 'title is required' });\n      return;\n    }\n    const doc = createDocument(db, title, content);\n    res.status(201).json(doc);\n  });\n\n  expressApp.get('/documents', (_req, res) => {\n    res.json(listDocuments(db));\n  });\n\n  expressApp.get('/documents/:id', (req, res) => {\n    const doc = getDocument(db, req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) { res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }); return; }\n    res.json(doc);\n  });\n\n  expressApp.put('/documents/:id', (req, res) => {\n    const existing = getDocument(db, req.params.id);\n    if (!existing) { res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }); return; }\n    const { title, content } = req.body as { title?: string; content?: string };\n    const newTitle = title ?? existing.title;\n    const newContent = content ?? existing.content;\n    // Use a synthetic op for REST updates\n    const op: Operation = { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: '' };\n    const updated = updateDocument(db, req.params.id, newContent, op);\n    if (!updated) { res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }); return; }\n    // Update title separately if changed\n    if (newTitle !== existing.title) {\n      db.prepare('UPDATE documents SET title = ? WHERE id = ?').run(newTitle, req.params.id);\n      updated.title = newTitle;\n    }\n    res.json(updated);\n  });\n\n  expressApp.delete('/documents/:id', (req, res) => {\n    const deleted = deleteDocument(db, req.params.id);\n    if (!deleted) { res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }); return; }\n    res.status(204).end();\n  });\n\n  expressApp.get('/documents/:id/history', (req, res) => {\n    const doc = getDocument(db, req.params.id);\n    if (!doc) { res.status(404).json({ error: 'Not found' }); return; }\n    res.json(getVersionHistory(db, req.params.id));\n  });\n\n  // --- WebSocket ---\n\n  httpServer.on('upgrade', (request, socket, head) => {\n    const url = new URL(request.url ?? '/', `http://localhost`);\n    const match = url.pathname.match(/^\\/ws\\/([^/]+)$/);\n    if (!match) {\n      socket.destroy();\n      return;\n    }\n    const docId = match[1];\n    const doc = getDocument(db, docId);\n    if (!doc) {\n      socket.destroy();\n      return;\n    }\n    wss.handleUpgrade(request, socket, head, (ws) => {\n      handleClient(ws, docId, doc, db, docSessions);\n    });\n  });\n\n  function handleClient(\n    ws: WebSocket,\n    docId: string,\n    initialDoc: Document,\n    db: Database.Database,\n    sessions: Map<string, DocSession>\n  ) {\n    if (!sessions.has(docId)) {\n      sessions.set(docId, { clients: new Set() });\n    }\n    const session = sessions.get(docId)!;\n\n    const client: ClientState = { ws, docId, version: initialDoc.version };\n    session.clients.add(client);\n\n    // Send initial sync\n    ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n      type: 'sync',\n      content: initialDoc.content,\n      version: initialDoc.version,\n    }));\n\n    ws.on('message', (data) => {\n      let msg: { type: string; op?: Operation; version?: number };\n      try {\n        msg = JSON.parse(data.toString()) as { type: string; op?: Operation; version?: number };\n      } catch {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Invalid JSON' }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      if (msg.type !== 'op' || !msg.op || typeof msg.version !== 'number') {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Invalid op message' }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Validate op\n      const op = msg.op;\n      if (!validateOp(op)) {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Malformed operation' }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const currentDoc = getDocument(db, docId);\n      if (!currentDoc) {\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'error', message: 'Document not found' }));\n        return;\n      }\n\n      // Transform against concurrent ops\n      let transformedOp = op;\n      const clientVersion = msg.version;\n\n      // Get all server ops since client's version\n      const serverOps = getOpsSinceVersion(db, docId, clientVersion);\n      for (const serverOp of serverOps) {\n        [transformedOp] = transform(transformedOp, serverOp);\n      }\n\n      // Apply transformed op to current content\n      const newContent = applyOp(currentDoc.content, transformedOp);\n      const updated = updateDocument(db, docId, newContent, transformedOp);\n      if (!updated) return;\n\n      // Update client version\n      client.version = updated.version;\n\n      // Broadcast to other clients\n      const broadcastMsg = JSON.stringify({\n        type: 'op',\n        op: transformedOp,\n        version: updated.version,\n      });\n\n      for (const other of session.clients) {\n        if (other !== client && other.ws.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN) {\n          other.ws.send(broadcastMsg);\n          other.version = updated.version;\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Ack to sender\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'ack', version: updated.version }));\n    });\n\n    ws.on('close', () => {\n      session.clients.delete(client);\n      if (session.clients.size === 0) {\n        sessions.delete(docId);\n      }\n    });\n\n    ws.on('error', () => {\n      session.clients.delete(client);\n    });\n  }\n\n  function validateOp(op: unknown): op is Operation {\n    if (!op || typeof op !== 'object') return false;\n    const o = op as Record<string, unknown>;\n    if (o.type === 'insert') {\n      return typeof o.pos === 'number' && o.pos >= 0 && typeof o.text === 'string';\n    }\n    if (o.type === 'delete') {\n      return typeof o.pos === 'number' && o.pos >= 0 && typeof o.length === 'number' && o.length >= 0;\n    }\n    return false;\n  }\n\n  function getOpsSinceVersion(db: Database.Database, docId: string, fromVersion: number): Operation[] {\n    const rows = db.prepare(\n      `SELECT operation FROM versions WHERE document_id = ? AND version > ? ORDER BY version ASC`\n    ).all(docId, fromVersion) as { operation: string | null }[];\n    return rows\n      .filter(r => r.operation !== null)\n      .map(r => JSON.parse(r.operation!) as Operation);\n  }\n\n  const start = (port = 0): Promise<number> => {\n    return new Promise((resolve) => {\n      httpServer.listen(port, () => {\n        const addr = httpServer.address();\n        const actualPort = typeof addr === 'object' && addr ? addr.port : port;\n        resolve(actualPort);\n      });\n    });\n  };\n\n  const stop = (): Promise<void> => {\n    return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n      // Close all WS connections\n      wss.clients.forEach(ws => ws.terminate());\n      wss.close(() => {\n        httpServer.close((err) => {\n          db.close();\n          if (err) reject(err);\n          else resolve();\n        });\n      });\n    });\n  };\n\n  return { app: expressApp, start, stop };\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run REST tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/rest.test.ts 2>&1\n```\nExpected: All REST tests pass\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add src/server.ts tests/rest.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"feat: add Express REST API routes\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: WebSocket Integration Tests\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `tests/websocket.test.ts`\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 3\n\n**Step 1: Write WebSocket tests**\n\nCreate `tests/websocket.test.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { describe, it, expect, beforeEach, afterEach } from 'vitest';\nimport { WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport request from 'supertest';\nimport { createApp } from '../src/server.js';\n\ntype AppInstance = Awaited<ReturnType<typeof createApp>>;\n\nlet appInstance: ReturnType<typeof createApp>;\nlet port: number;\n\nfunction wsConnect(docId: string): Promise<WebSocket> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${port}/ws/${docId}`);\n    ws.once('open', () => resolve(ws));\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction waitForMessage(ws: WebSocket): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    ws.once('message', (data) => {\n      try { resolve(JSON.parse(data.toString())); }\n      catch (e) { reject(e); }\n    });\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction sendAndWait(ws: WebSocket, msg: unknown, waitWs?: WebSocket): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n  const target = waitWs ?? ws;\n  const p = waitForMessage(target);\n  ws.send(JSON.stringify(msg));\n  return p;\n}\n\nbeforeEach(async () => {\n  appInstance = createApp(':memory:');\n  port = await appInstance.start(0);\n});\n\nafterEach(async () => {\n  await appInstance.stop();\n});\n\ndescribe('WebSocket sync', () => {\n  it('sends sync message on connect', async () => {\n    const doc = await request(appInstance.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Test', content: 'hello' });\n    const ws = await wsConnect(doc.body.id);\n    const msg = await waitForMessage(ws);\n    expect(msg.type).toBe('sync');\n    expect(msg.content).toBe('hello');\n    ws.close();\n  });\n\n  it('rejects connection for nonexistent document', async () => {\n    await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {\n      const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${port}/ws/nonexistent`);\n      ws.once('close', () => resolve());\n      ws.once('error', () => resolve());\n    });\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('WebSocket operations', () => {\n  it('applies insert and sends ack', async () => {\n    const doc = await request(appInstance.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'T', content: 'hello' });\n    const ws = await wsConnect(doc.body.id);\n    await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n    const ack = await sendAndWait(ws, {\n      type: 'op',\n      version: 1,\n      op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' },\n    });\n    expect(ack.type).toBe('ack');\n    expect(ack.version).toBe(2);\n\n    const updated = await request(appInstance.app).get(`/documents/${doc.body.id}`);\n    expect(updated.body.content).toBe('hello world');\n    ws.close();\n  });\n\n  it('broadcasts op to other clients', async () => {\n    const doc = await request(appInstance.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'T', content: 'hello' });\n    const ws1 = await wsConnect(doc.body.id);\n    const ws2 = await wsConnect(doc.body.id);\n\n    await waitForMessage(ws1); // sync\n    await waitForMessage(ws2); // sync\n\n    // ws1 sends op, ws2 should receive broadcast\n    const broadcastPromise = waitForMessage(ws2);\n    ws1.send(JSON.stringify({\n      type: 'op',\n      version: 1,\n      op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: '!' },\n    }));\n    const broadcast = await broadcastPromise;\n    expect(broadcast.type).toBe('op');\n    expect((broadcast.op as { text: string }).text).toBe('!');\n\n    ws1.close();\n    ws2.close();\n  });\n\n  it('rejects invalid op', async () => {\n    const doc = await request(appInstance.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'T', content: 'hi' });\n    const ws = await wsConnect(doc.body.id);\n    await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n    const err = await sendAndWait(ws, { type: 'op', version: 1, op: { type: 'bad' } });\n    expect(err.type).toBe('error');\n    ws.close();\n  });\n\n  it('rejects malformed JSON', async () => {\n    const doc = await request(appInstance.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'T', content: 'hi' });\n    const ws = await wsConnect(doc.body.id);\n    await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n    const p = waitForMessage(ws);\n    ws.send('not json');\n    const err = await p;\n    expect(err.type).toBe('error');\n    ws.close();\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Concurrent edits convergence', () => {\n  it('two simultaneous inserts both preserved and converge', async () => {\n    const doc = await request(appInstance.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'T', content: 'hello' });\n    const docId = doc.body.id;\n\n    const ws1 = await wsConnect(docId);\n    const ws2 = await wsConnect(docId);\n    await waitForMessage(ws1); // sync v1\n    await waitForMessage(ws2); // sync v1\n\n    // Both clients send ops based on version 1 simultaneously\n    // ws1 inserts 'A' at pos 0: 'Ahello'\n    // ws2 inserts 'B' at pos 5 (end): 'helloB'\n    // After transform: both should be preserved → 'AhelloB'\n\n    const ws2BroadcastPromise = waitForMessage(ws2); // will get ws1's op broadcast\n    ws1.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', version: 1, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'A' } }));\n    const ack1Promise = waitForMessage(ws1);\n    const ack1 = await ack1Promise;\n    expect(ack1.type).toBe('ack');\n\n    // Now ws2 sends its op (still at version 1 - concurrent)\n    const ack2Promise = waitForMessage(ws2);\n    ws2.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', version: 1, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'B' } }));\n\n    const ack2 = await ack2Promise;\n    // ack2 might be the broadcast from ws1, or the ack from ws2's op\n    // We need to be careful here - ws2 may receive broadcast before its ack\n\n    // Wait for final state\n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 100));\n\n    const final = await request(appInstance.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    // Both 'A' and 'B' should be in the content\n    expect(final.body.content).toContain('A');\n    expect(final.body.content).toContain('B');\n    expect(final.body.content).toContain('hello');\n\n    ws1.close();\n    ws2.close();\n  });\n\n  it('handles 10 concurrent clients', async () => {\n    const doc = await request(appInstance.app)\n      .post('/documents')\n      .send({ title: 'Stress', content: '' });\n    const docId = doc.body.id;\n\n    const clients = await Promise.all(\n      Array.from({ length: 10 }, () => wsConnect(docId))\n    );\n\n    // Wait for all sync messages\n    await Promise.all(clients.map(ws => waitForMessage(ws)));\n\n    // Each client inserts a unique character\n    const chars = 'ABCDEFGHIJ';\n    const acks = await Promise.all(\n      clients.map((ws, i) => {\n        const p = waitForMessage(ws);\n        ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n          type: 'op',\n          version: 1,\n          op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: chars[i] },\n        }));\n        return p;\n      })\n    );\n\n    // Wait for all ops to be processed\n    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));\n\n    const final = await request(appInstance.app).get(`/documents/${docId}`);\n    // All characters should appear in final content\n    for (const ch of chars) {\n      expect(final.body.content).toContain(ch);\n    }\n\n    clients.forEach(ws => ws.close());\n  });\n});\n```\n\n**Step 2: Run tests**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/websocket.test.ts 2>&1\n```\n\n**Step 3: Fix any issues found in tests**\n\nDebug and fix as needed.\n\n**Step 4: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/websocket.test.ts\ngit commit -m \"test: add WebSocket collaboration tests\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Build, Lint, and Final Verification\n\n**Files:** All source files\n\n**Dependencies:** Task 4\n\n**Step 1: Run full test suite**\n\n```bash\nnpm test 2>&1\n```\nExpected: All tests pass\n\n**Step 2: Run build**\n\n```bash\nnpm run build 2>&1\n```\nExpected: No errors\n\n**Step 3: Run lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm run lint 2>&1\n```\nExpected: No errors. Fix any lint issues found.\n\n**Step 4: Final commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A\ngit commit -m \"chore: final verification - all tests pass, build clean\"\n```\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
