 doesn't call `request(appInstance.app)` first, it just directly tries to connect with a bad doc ID. The connection opens, then gets destroyed.\n\nActually let me think again: in \"sends sync message on connect\", the test:\n1. Creates a doc via `request(appInstance.app)` - REST call through supertest's temp server\n2. Tries to WebSocket connect to `localhost:${port}/ws/${doc.body.id}`\n\nFor step 2 to work, the doc needs to exist in our database. But the REST call in step 1 went to a DIFFERENT server (supertest's temp server) with a DIFFERENT database (since `createApp(':memory:')` creates a new DB). Wait - no! The supertest `request(expressApp)` uses the SAME express app instance and the SAME db connection. The `expressApp` has the routes already set up with the db closure.\n\nActually the Express routes close over `db` in the `createApp` function. Both the supertest requests and the HTTP server use the same `expressApp` instance. So the db should be shared. Documents created via `request(appInstance.app)` should be visible to WebSocket connections on `httpServer`.\n\nLet me verify this theory by changing the test to use `fetch` directly to create the document:\n\nActually, let me check something - what if the connection is hanging because `wss.handleUpgrade` is blocking or not calling the callback? Let me add some logging:\n\nActually let me try a completely different approach: use `fetch` instead of supertest in the WebSocket tests, since both should work with the already-started server:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":369,"cache_read_input_tokens":69522,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":369},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9afc7e8f-bb6c-44d5-b274-f24facf40226","uuid":"77989317-79cd-4d50-8a87-e7730f25a674"}
