+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TQ1V18u6Y8nhP5SLVqP9fs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"WebSocket works perfectly! The issue was with the original test structure using `beforeEach`/`afterEach` for server setup. The problem was that `port` and `baseUrl` are module-level variables that might not be properly scoped between tests. Let me check if maybe when running multiple tests, the `beforeEach` isn't running properly or `port` gets stale.\n\nActually, the real issue was probably that `appInstance.stop()` in `afterEach` was resolving the port issue but `port` was still the old value for the next test. But wait - the module-level `let port: number` is reassigned in each `beforeEach`. That should work.\n\nLet me look at the problem from another angle - when all tests fail simultaneously and all timeout at exactly 10000ms, it strongly suggests the tests are running in parallel and the `beforeEach`/`afterEach` for each test is interfering. Vitest runs tests in parallel by default within a file!\n\nWhen `afterEach` calls `app.stop()`, it closes the httpServer. But then the next test's `beforeEach` creates a new server. However, because tests run concurrently within the same worker, `port` might be overwritten by one test's `beforeEach` before another test has finished using it.\n\nThe fix is to add `poolOptions: { forks: { singleThread: true } }` to vitest config, OR better, restructure tests to not use module-level state.\n\nActually wait - vitest runs test files in parallel but runs tests WITHIN a file sequentially by default. Unless `concurrent` is enabled. Let me verify by checking if the issue is that my `beforeEach` isn't awaited properly.\n\nActually - let me just rewrite the websocket test to be simpler and not use `beforeEach`/`afterEach` at all:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":389,"cache_read_input_tokens":83797,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":389},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9afc7e8f-bb6c-44d5-b274-f24facf40226","uuid":"369d7815-eee1-4fe1-8329-8122a8f02293"}
+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TQ1V18u6Y8nhP5SLVqP9fs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FFa3WTBKFPNn6axa8mnqMR","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/tests/websocket.test.ts","content":"import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';\nimport { WebSocket } from 'ws';\nimport { createApp } from '../src/server.js';\n\ntype AppInstance = ReturnType<typeof createApp>;\n\nasync function setup(): Promise<{ app: AppInstance; port: number; baseUrl: string }> {\n  const app = createApp(':memory:');\n  const port = await app.start(0);\n  return { app, port, baseUrl: `http://localhost:${port}` };\n}\n\nasync function createDoc(\n  baseUrl: string,\n  title: string,\n  content: string\n): Promise<{ id: string; version: number }> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${baseUrl}/documents`, {\n    method: 'POST',\n    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n    body: JSON.stringify({ title, content }),\n  });\n  return res.json() as Promise<{ id: string; version: number }>;\n}\n\nasync function getDoc(\n  baseUrl: string,\n  id: string\n): Promise<{ content: string; version: number }> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${baseUrl}/documents/${id}`);\n  return res.json() as Promise<{ content: string; version: number }>;\n}\n\nasync function getHistory(\n  baseUrl: string,\n  id: string\n): Promise<Array<{ version: number }>> {\n  const res = await fetch(`${baseUrl}/documents/${id}/history`);\n  return res.json() as Promise<Array<{ version: number }>>;\n}\n\nfunction wsConnect(port: number, docId: string): Promise<WebSocket> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${port}/ws/${docId}`);\n    ws.once('open', () => resolve(ws));\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\nfunction waitForMessage(ws: WebSocket): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    ws.once('message', (data) => {\n      try {\n        resolve(JSON.parse(data.toString()) as Record<string, unknown>);\n      } catch (e) {\n        reject(e);\n      }\n    });\n    ws.once('error', reject);\n  });\n}\n\ndescribe('WebSocket sync', () => {\n  it('sends sync message on connect', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'Test', 'hello');\n      const ws = await wsConnect(port, doc.id);\n      const msg = await waitForMessage(ws);\n      expect(msg.type).toBe('sync');\n      expect(msg.content).toBe('hello');\n      ws.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n\n  it('rejects connection for nonexistent document', async () => {\n    const { app, port } = await setup();\n    try {\n      await new Promise<void>((resolve) => {\n        const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:${port}/ws/nonexistent`);\n        ws.once('close', () => resolve());\n        ws.once('error', () => resolve());\n      });\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('WebSocket operations', () => {\n  it('applies insert and sends ack', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'T', 'hello');\n      const ws = await wsConnect(port, doc.id);\n      await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n      const ackPromise = waitForMessage(ws);\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n        type: 'op',\n        version: 1,\n        op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' },\n      }));\n      const ack = await ackPromise;\n      expect(ack.type).toBe('ack');\n      expect(ack.version).toBe(2);\n\n      const updated = await getDoc(baseUrl, doc.id);\n      expect(updated.content).toBe('hello world');\n      ws.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n\n  it('applies delete and sends ack', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'T', 'hello world');\n      const ws = await wsConnect(port, doc.id);\n      await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n      const ackPromise = waitForMessage(ws);\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n        type: 'op',\n        version: 1,\n        op: { type: 'delete', pos: 5, length: 6 },\n      }));\n      const ack = await ackPromise;\n      expect(ack.type).toBe('ack');\n\n      const updated = await getDoc(baseUrl, doc.id);\n      expect(updated.content).toBe('hello');\n      ws.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n\n  it('broadcasts op to other clients', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'T', 'hello');\n      const ws1 = await wsConnect(port, doc.id);\n      const ws2 = await wsConnect(port, doc.id);\n\n      await waitForMessage(ws1); // sync\n      await waitForMessage(ws2); // sync\n\n      const broadcastPromise = waitForMessage(ws2);\n      ws1.send(JSON.stringify({\n        type: 'op',\n        version: 1,\n        op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: '!' },\n      }));\n\n      const broadcast = await broadcastPromise;\n      expect(broadcast.type).toBe('op');\n      expect((broadcast.op as { text: string }).text).toBe('!');\n\n      ws1.close();\n      ws2.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n\n  it('does not broadcast to sender', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'T', 'hello');\n      const ws = await wsConnect(port, doc.id);\n      await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n      const ackPromise = waitForMessage(ws);\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n        type: 'op',\n        version: 1,\n        op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'X' },\n      }));\n      const ack = await ackPromise;\n      expect(ack.type).toBe('ack');\n      ws.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n\n  it('rejects invalid op type', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'T', 'hi');\n      const ws = await wsConnect(port, doc.id);\n      await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n      const errPromise = waitForMessage(ws);\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', version: 1, op: { type: 'bad_op' } }));\n      const err = await errPromise;\n      expect(err.type).toBe('error');\n      ws.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n\n  it('rejects malformed JSON', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'T', 'hi');\n      const ws = await wsConnect(port, doc.id);\n      await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n      const errPromise = waitForMessage(ws);\n      ws.send('not json');\n      const err = await errPromise;\n      expect(err.type).toBe('error');\n      ws.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n\n  it('rejects op message without version field', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'T', 'hi');\n      const ws = await wsConnect(port, doc.id);\n      await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n      const errPromise = waitForMessage(ws);\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'X' } }));\n      const err = await errPromise;\n      expect(err.type).toBe('error');\n      ws.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n});\n\ndescribe('Concurrent edits convergence', () => {\n  it('two simultaneous inserts both preserved', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'T', 'hello');\n      const docId = doc.id;\n\n      const ws1 = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n      const ws2 = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n      await waitForMessage(ws1); // sync v1\n      await waitForMessage(ws2); // sync v1\n\n      // ws1 inserts 'A' at pos 0 → 'Ahello'\n      // ws2 inserts 'B' at pos 5 → 'helloB' (concurrent, also at version 1)\n      // After OT: both preserved\n\n      const ack1Promise = waitForMessage(ws1);\n      ws1.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', version: 1, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: 'A' } }));\n      const ack1 = await ack1Promise;\n      expect(ack1.type).toBe('ack');\n\n      // ws2 sends its op (concurrent with ws1's at version 1)\n      const ws2Messages: Record<string, unknown>[] = [];\n      const ws2DonePromise = new Promise<void>((resolve) => {\n        const handler = (data: Buffer) => {\n          const msg = JSON.parse(data.toString()) as Record<string, unknown>;\n          ws2Messages.push(msg);\n          if (msg.type === 'ack' || ws2Messages.length >= 2) {\n            ws2.off('message', handler);\n            resolve();\n          }\n        };\n        ws2.on('message', handler);\n        ws2.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', version: 1, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: 'B' } }));\n      });\n      await ws2DonePromise;\n\n      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 100));\n\n      const final = await getDoc(baseUrl, docId);\n      const content = final.content;\n      expect(content).toContain('A');\n      expect(content).toContain('B');\n      expect(content).toContain('hello');\n\n      ws1.close();\n      ws2.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n\n  it('handles 10 concurrent clients without corruption', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'Stress', '');\n      const docId = doc.id;\n\n      const clients = await Promise.all(\n        Array.from({ length: 10 }, () => wsConnect(port, docId))\n      );\n\n      // Wait for all sync messages\n      await Promise.all(clients.map(ws => waitForMessage(ws)));\n\n      // Each client inserts a unique character at pos 0 based on version 1\n      const chars = 'ABCDEFGHIJ';\n      await Promise.all(\n        clients.map((ws, i) => {\n          ws.send(JSON.stringify({\n            type: 'op',\n            version: 1,\n            op: { type: 'insert', pos: 0, text: chars[i] },\n          }));\n          return Promise.resolve();\n        })\n      );\n\n      // Wait for all ops to settle\n      await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));\n\n      const final = await getDoc(baseUrl, docId);\n      const content = final.content;\n\n      // All 10 characters must appear in the document\n      for (const ch of chars) {\n        expect(content).toContain(ch);\n      }\n      // Document should have exactly 10 characters\n      expect(content.length).toBe(10);\n\n      clients.forEach(ws => ws.close());\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n\n  it('version history tracks all operations', async () => {\n    const { app, port, baseUrl } = await setup();\n    try {\n      const doc = await createDoc(baseUrl, 'T', 'hello');\n      const docId = doc.id;\n\n      const ws = await wsConnect(port, docId);\n      await waitForMessage(ws); // sync\n\n      const ack1Promise = waitForMessage(ws);\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', version: 1, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 5, text: ' world' } }));\n      await ack1Promise;\n\n      const ack2Promise = waitForMessage(ws);\n      ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'op', version: 2, op: { type: 'insert', pos: 11, text: '!' } }));\n      await ack2Promise;\n\n      const history = await getHistory(baseUrl, docId);\n      expect(history).toHaveLength(3);\n      expect(history[0].version).toBe(1);\n      expect(history[1].version).toBe(2);\n      expect(history[2].version).toBe(3);\n\n      ws.close();\n    } finally {\n      await app.stop();\n    }\n  });\n});\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":389,"cache_read_input_tokens":83797,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_i